SIMPLE: unctuous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unctuous
<hw>Unc"tu*ous</hw> <pr>(?; 135)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>onctueux</ets>, LL. <ets>unctuosus</ets>, fr. L. <ets>unctus</ets>
anointment, fr. <ets>ungere</ets>, <ets>unctum</ets>, to anoint. See
<er>Unguent</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of the nature or quality of an
unguent or ointment; fatty; oily; greasy.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The
<xex>unctuous</xex> cheese.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Longfellow.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Having a smooth, greasy feel, as certain
minerals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Bland; suave; also, tender; fervid; <as>as, an
<ex>unctuous</ex> speech</as>; sometimes, insincerely suave or
fervid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Unc"tu*ous*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Unc"tu*ous*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unculpable</ent>⟦br⟧
